Qty.
1 onion.
Little bit of soy sauce.
1 carrot.
1 green capsicum.
Some hot sauce.
Many chilies.

Instructions.
1. Pour a lot of oil to cover the bottom of the bowl.

2. When the oil gets hot enough, fry onions for a little 
bit, then add chilies. 
   
2. A little bit later, add the carrot, and then the capsicum.

3. Fry for a little bit and add Szechuan chutney, hot sauce,
ketchup and soy sauce. Later, add a spoon of vinegar.

4. Put on basmati rice until it is 80% or 90% finished.

5. Add basmati rice to the tadka, mix well, and cook a little.
